The Golden Fleece or Ram is said to have been dedicated by Phyneas to Jupiter, on his arrival at Colchis: he consecrated 'the skin in the Grove of Mars, called it‘ the Golden Fleece from its colour, and, as it was said, had it guarded hy bulls breathing fire, and a watchful dragon that never slept.

In the Phoenician langnage, Gaza signifies either a treasure or a fleece; Sasu· a wall, or a bull; and in that ancient langnage, brass, imm, and a dragon were all expressed by the same word.
